profile_positions.description:
- Lead on the preparation and implementation of the WG work plan: The work is done in cooperation with the relevant member of EUROCITIES staff (policy advisor, project coordinator, support officer), and in coordination with the forum chair and forum steering committee. The WG work plan should be guided by the forum strategy and work programme, set specific and measurable goals, including a clear hierarchy of priorities, and provide an indicative implementation timeline; 
- Call WG meetings: While allowing for flexibility, the thematic focus of a WG meeting should be guided by the WG work plan and determined at the start of each year; 
- Report regularly on WG activities to the forum; 
- Prepare agendas for meetings: The work is done in cooperation with the relevant member of EUROCITIES staff;
- Prepare minutes of meetings in cooperation with the relevant member of staff (including list of participants, issues addressed, decisions taken, way forward); 
- Follow up on relevant policy work, in cooperation with the EUROCITIES team; 
- Participate in meetings of the EU Urban Agenda Partnership on Inclusion of Migrants and Refugees (depending on availability and topic relevance); 
- Report annually to the forum chair by a date set by the relevant member of EUROCITIES staff and the chair to have the report ready for consolidation with the other WG reports by early January; 
- Provide articles on the outputs of WG meetings that can be used e.g. for the EUROCITIES website or flash e-mails. This work is done in cooperation with the relevant member of EUROCITIES staff.

